Comments: Make it easier for processing invoices through Corporate with sub/teachers account.
The representative answered my email inquiry quickly.

I asked about how the school gave us specific code to put in and specific instructions to not use the teacher and school search. Your customer service reps informed me to notify the school that it is no longer necessary. It is not appropriate to have me notify them when you are the ones with the contract with the school. Unprofessional. I should not be told to notify the school of your removal of the code.

The customer service reps I talked with tried their best to help me with my issue, but neither of them were successful. My case was transferred to the tech department, but I have not heard anything else about it, nor was I given a contact to follow up on the issue. As of right now, our school cannot order Scholastic books through book clubs because of this issue.
Scholastic has always been great and anwering my order or points questions. I appreciate their knowle and kind staff

I was inquiring about the birthday gift certificates for students. I was told at this point that they are not available. Im hoping that will change and scholastic will offer them again. Im hoping that you will again make the scholastic birthday gift certificates available.
Great to work with and replied to email very fast!!

I am not a fan of the set due dates that Scholastic put in place. I liked having the flexibility to accommodate families and functions at our school. The decreased 'free' books, coupons, and points earned is also a concern for me, as I regularly used Scholastic to stock and upgrade my classroom library.  I believe this protocol will greatly impact the amount of new books I can add to my library.  However, I do like the move to fewer flyers.

I am upset about old promotions that no longer exist. This might lead me to not spending as much money or going to another business to order books. I am very disappointed about past offers not being an offer anymore like the book of the week and $1 book room after a certain amount of money is spent on a class order. I feel that buying books is becoming more and more expensive which is not feasible for some of my students.
I was disappointed that I am unable to set my own due date Would like to set my own due date and be able to edit letters to parents
Response was very quick, and taken care of right away.

I want to be able to change my order due dates each month. It's ridiculous that I can't. We teachers know our schedule and what works best for us; not anybody at Scholastic knows this. Also, your customer service representative that was assigned to me was quite ignorant and curt. How disappointing.

The customer service was just fine, however I'm disappointed in the changes that have been made regarding student ordering. Going to strictly online ordering is disappointing. We have families with circumstances that keep them from being able to order online.  I was provided a less then convenient way to help these families order and especially since tax is now in addition to the price shown in the flyers this makes the solution that was provided even more inconvenient. I am hesitant to even offer Scholastic Book Clubs as abest option for families to purchase books for their children.
If the flyer had a link to the book order so I could click on the book and order it from there.

I'm disappointed with the changes in ordering strictly on line and no information was sent to us about it.  I have been ordering for 27 years and nothing was explained about the changes and no info to send home. The parents are suppose to figure it out on their own on the back of the order form. Again, I would have appreciated info about the changes this year in the order forms.  I was waiting for other order forms to be sent out and had to research it on my own to figure the new procedures out!
I think the person who responded did a great job but I still can't locate the parent letters to attach to the flyers to send home. I need the parent letters to attach to the flyers to send home.

The woman that helped me out today was very patient and kind. I love that it was an enjoyable call, in addition to her helping solve my issue. I am one happy customer and pleased with the service I received!

Your new ordering system is not working out for families that are unable to go online or have a language barrier where they can't understand what to do when they're online.  Giving parents the option to pay online or in person via teacher was great but now it's all online. Some parents are continuing to pay with checks and giving it to me, so I was told by rep there's a tax that is added since I am paying as a teacher.  That is SO wrong!  There is NO option for families to pay through teachers anymore.  And if they do, we as teachers, are responsible for all the taxes because we're not going to be asking parents for another dollar once the check is written.  I usually have a lot of students ordering but this is the FIRST year where I only have 2 and that's it.  I asked the parents and students why and they said it's too much of a hassle.  If you are looking for a way to have less books ordered by parents who cant go online then it's working.

I am not a parent. I have never had my own children.  I am an educator. I went in to update my information and spend my points and you down graded my account to parent and denied my request. I am a University of Missouri 4-H Youth Specialist. My contract litterally says "90% Extension Teaching".   And then I get hung up on when I am being transfered and no one calls me back?! You have my phone number in multiple places. This is ridiculous.

The rep gave me the answer I sought, but it is something new that Scholastic is doing thinking they are helping teachers. I didn't want that. So I created my own parent letter with my own due date. Let teachers have control on due dates again.

I am very disappointed in the changes that have been made to book clubs the past 2 years. This year we cannot manage our own due dates and you aren't sending flyers home anymore. That is the best part of getting books is being able to take the flyer home. This will be the last year I will be using scholastic.

I was not given an option to edit the date of the book orders. I would like to be able to do this as some of our families have different pay days and they asked the orders to be turned in near that date. This survey took a little time to complete because I had to look for the "next" button.
I was cut off and there was no answer at all
I am simply in awe of how quickly I was able to be helped. The Scholastic customer service team and IT team did a great job helping me out.
Return Club leo so I can order booktrust books for my class in Spanish. Please return CLUB LEO

I am frustrated with how the new bonus point shop is laid out.  I am also frustrated that iPads are no longer available, as well as many other items I have been keeping an eye on. Please bring back the options to purchase iPads and Apple Watches with bonus points.  Thank you!
The chat format worked well and was efficient; however, some of the changes that were made in your program I do not care for.
I am very sad to see the dollar book store and the weekly $1 books are no longer available.
I do not like the new way the order dates work. The employee interaction was fine.
Great customer service through the chat feature.  We also asked for a follow up email so that we could remember the steps to follow and we were able to get that right away.  Thank you!

I know the people answering the emails have no power over the concerns I had, so I asked for information on who to contact.  All I got was that my concerns would be forwarded.  No actual answer to my question and no acknowledgment of my concerns. I want to set my own date and I want my students to be able to order with paper slips and not be forced to order online.  It is making it harder for students to get books.

Received a rolling cart with 2 broken drawers. The cart has already been put together and cannot be mailed back. Requesting replacement of the 2 drawers. Was told someone would be in contact with me and no one has reached out. Feel the customer rep only said that so she could get off the phone.
I hope you will bring back the gift cards to buy using points.  I was disappointed that you no longer offer gift cards for teachers to purchase using bonus points.
Unfortunately, I have to ask my head teacher to submit the large order, however we are friends and she would give me the points earned should I ask. Well use them for our classroom- all good!
1.00$ books  More sets for holidays  Your prices seem very high

I sent a check for 300$ to scholastic and put an account number on  later they gave me a dif account number and told me the one i ised was an old account.  I was told i would hear from scholastics when check was received and heard nothing.
Id like to be able to edit my due date and not have one set for me Id like to be able to edit my due date and not have it set for me

I just don't like the new fliers it's way to expensive for families. There are no $2 books for low income families. We may not be able to order from scholastic this year because there expensive. Which is sad and disappointing.
My question was answered. I'm waiting for my paper flyers to arrive in the mail.

I tried to use bonus points in June to purchase target gift cards to use towards and iPad. I didnt have enough points for the iPad via scholastic. Now it turned out you dont do target gift cards. Seems like something could have been arranged. I asked preciously to pay the difference between my 30000 points and the price of the iPad  To say I am disappointed is an understatement. Especially given my administration of scholastic book clubs in my classroom.
The email response was quick and understandable.
It's frustrating that dates have been preset to have orders submitted. It feels like not enough outreach was done to explain this big change.
You have changed the way parents can order without even letting teachers know--very disappointed.

I do not like recent changes that were put in place and feel like it's a disadvantage to teachers. I am frustrated that I cannot pick my due date. I cannot order books for my students or classroom until a parent puts in an order - unless I pay for shipping (which I refuse to do). This means, if a parent waits until the middle of October to buy books, I have to wait a whole 2 months to get books for my classroom. Plus, the more money that is spent, the more bonus points I earn. So I'm at a complete disadvantage to earn free books for my classroom with bonus points by putting in orders right away. If a parent puts in an order in September, I purposely won't submit that order until October so that I can try to build up my bonus points. That's ridiculous for both parties involved. You're not making anything "easier" for teachers, as was described to me in my live chat. Picking a due date isn't work for teachers. These new protocols make things harder for teachers, which is a shame on Scholastic.

I do not like the fact that the due date for the Scholastic Flyers are already set for the teachers.  We should be able to set the due date if we want.  There should be an optional choice to do it.  I have to print the copy of the teacher letter to parents, white out the date and hand write in my due date that I am setting.
How do I change the date the book order is due by?

I asked a question of Scholastic and never received an answer about the Macbook in the teacher store. I have been saving and working for years to save points to obtain this computer. I finally received an email from your company only to say that it is not available. My school and I have been loyal customers for years. I want Scholastic to find a way to make this happen - one computer for all the points I have saved up for this for years and the fact that I contacted your company about it last year with no response.

My issues was with your ordering on line.  When I first went in to release an on line order, it told me I had earned $10 to spend right now.  I input one book then went to continue shopping for another book and then it would not longer allow me to order any books.  I was just told it was an error on your end and that it would be reported

My customer service representative was very helpful and I would rate her a 5.  My disappointment is in your reduction of $2 books to only one per month.  I think that this limits the number of families that can order.  As a teacher, it also limits the number of books that I can order for my students.  I have a program where every student  in my class gets a $2 book once a month.  Now I have to choose the one book you have to offer.
The representative was very helpful and accurate. I would have just preferred a different answer.
They just told told me that I need to wait 7-10 business days. That didn't answer my question.  My questions was "I have not received any flyers yet this year."

I want to note that Julie Reel gave me excellent customer service.  She was well versed in the book trust program, which I really appreciated.  I feel she went above and beyond in providing customer service, reaching out to her manager when she did not know an answer, following up with me to make sure I had the correct contact information and any new information she received.  I truly felt like I was her top priority, even though I know she must field hundreds of calls a day.  I just wanted to reach out and let management know what a valuable resource Julie is to me.
I will wait and see how the ordering of books go this school year.  It has been very discouraging to see the few points and books in which I receive for promoting your product.  Lynn

The change away from teachers entering student orders, and away from estimated tax being included on flyer orders, is a change for the worse. In a low-resource community like my school, we have many parents who do not have credit cards, and some do not even have bank accounts; they operate with cash whenever possible. Those students will not be able to order books. Some students save up lunch money to buy books. Either allowing teachers to enter cash orders, or figuring tax into prices so we could accept them and pay through our own accounts, is really a needed service for me to continue to use Scholastic with my students.

Not teacher friendly for us to not be able to set up our own due dates.  I want to be able to change that online but it's not possible.  I do not want to have the due date in October when I sent the book order home in August.
So far I am happy with the process.  However, I can't give my final rating until I receive the replacement books I requested. I think it will be, just waiting for my replacement books.
Quick response to online chat and my question was answered.
My flyers are not here. They will not be here until the third week of school.

I do not like the autoship feature. I make a deadline that is more convenient for parents, based on when pay day may be, or the weekend to place an order. I do not like how it is automatically placed. I wish this feature could be turned off by teachers if they did not want to use it. I also had difficulty finding the phone number to call and speak to a representative.
Your sales associate was perfect, just SUPER bummed about the policy changes I was inquiring about I saved all my points for an iPad and now all you can get it junk

Nothing. The customer service rep listened. It isnt their fault that Scholastic has taken such a turn. I do not like the fact teachers cant sent their own due dates, the catalogs have hardly any selection and there will only be 6 this year. Also the dollar books are gone and the $5 for a dollar as well. This is a sad year. To resolve my concern: 1. Teacher should be able to select their own due dates. 2. Dollar books should return.  3  More selections in the catalogs.  4. More catalogs per year.
Please let teachers set book order due dates again.

Nothing I would really like to be able to set my own due date for book orders like I have been able to in the past.  I like to be able to have them due at specific times to ensure books that parents may want for holidays arrive before the holiday.  I also like to schedule due dates around our school Scholastic Book Fairs so they don't conflict.
Told people your changes in advance.

You make things more difficult for families that do t have online access to place orders. Why in the world you not give an option for parents to pay with a check and send their order into the teacher like they have always been able to do? Its discriminating and I will not participate. That and a mandatory due date are ridiculous. Anything to make things easier for your company with no regard for schools and families.
I like to being able to use the chat button and talk to someone right away

I contacted Scholastic because I had never received any back-to-school flyers. I have been a Golden Apple teacher for years and am disappointed that I cannot send flyers home this week as we start school. I hope my flyers arrive so I can place orders before the end of September. Once my flyers arrive, my concern will be resolved.
The CS rep. was fine, it was the answer that I did not like.  I am VERY disappointed in your dropping the 10,000 bonus points promotion in September.

The answer to my first email was that my flyers were already delivered. I would have rathered  you just sent out flyers. We will see if this has been resolved if I get flyers in Oct or have to call and ask for them again.
Supply books as you were supposed to
Nothing All of those "Ai" chatbots do what a normal google search does.

Bring back the teacher's ability to order books for students who pay with cash or check. Many of the families in our district do not have computers at home and prefer to pay for things with cash. Now you've put the record keeping on the teacher to keep track of which students order what. We have enough to do. I really hope you are listening to the customer.... Bring back three old ordering system where teachers enter student orders by student name.
I was able to get in, locate my item, order, and quickly go about my day.
They were super helpful with how I change my account to my new school. Very appreciative!
I really object to having my due dates preset for me and I am unhappy with the bonus catalog.
Also I had to change my password and it was very easy to navigate.
Didn't buy books yet. But we will be!    Thank you!
I love looking at the books and reading the descriptions before I buy them
The site is super easy to use and I find it very user friendly.
It was easy to submit both my kids order at once!
Your books are really cool thank you.
It was easy to add a student and change teachers for another thank you
The website isn't super easy to navigate.
I was making a payment, web-page is very easy to navigate.
I don't like your new system of automatic deadlines.
Seemed easy enough to navigate, I like the variety of options
Would love a grades selection for Babies and toddlers!
Thank you scholastic for providing affordable books!!
Great way to keep kids interested in reading
I love that you have a bigger selection of books in spanish
I was a teacher for years and always used Scholastic - Love you guys!!  Now I get to order as a grandma - Yay!!!
Starting a fundraising campaign was easier than I anticipated because  of the examples you provided.
I love being able to shop right from the flyer.
I love your site.  Very easy to use.  I usually receive catalogs at the beginning of the year.  I didn't this year.  This is the first time I ever had to request them.  Is this new?

I  purchased Scholastic Books for a very long time....through children, grandchildren and now a great grand child. These books are such a great value and worth even more as a quick and convenient way to improve reading, counting and social skills.
Thank you for making it easier to find the books that are $5 or less. I sent links to friends!
Very easy to find what I was looking for and more!
Site is great, easy to use.
Love the 2$ books of the week for my students!
Lack of Spanish books in bundles like the English ones.
I LOVE THAT YOU CAN ORDER DIRECTLY FROM THE FLYER.
Just browsing for the year and checking my club points and products available.  I like the new site updates!
Thank you for doing your best to make the site easy to maneuver through. I do prefer to hand out hard copies of your catalogs to my students , with the option to order on line.
will be back to order some books for grand daughter
My son was so excited to place his first book order! He enjoyed picking out the books and chose ones I think he will love!

I love how easy the site was to navigate. I especially love the feature where you can view the flyer and tap the books you want to buy. The flyer is where we picked things out so finding the books we wanted on the electronic flyer made it super simple to order.
On of the better infaces i have encountered.  Like the simplicity of ordering for one child versus another.  Well done.
I used the online chat.  Excellent
Thank you for having both affordable and wonderful books!
Easy-to-use once you get right page for ewallet. It's easy to set up but be sure to use correct amount because change is different.
Love the site more than the little flyers so much more
Thank you so much!!!  We love Scholastic!!!
After Clicking on item in flyer,  hard to go back. Browser back exits the flyer. Annoying
I wish there werent so many toys. We have lots of toys. There were several books we didnt get because they were attached to a toy.
I couldn't find where to put the classroom code in that the teacher sent home with the flyers.

I want to be able to set my due date.    I will try sending home an order, but I won't send them home every month.  The books are just too expensive now.  I don't like the new flyers with the "riddles, how to draw, crossword puzzles, etc.  What happened to the $1 books you used to offer teachers?  Judy Newman?

Tried to send digital order email to parents, but I didn't have the email server that would work.  I made a copy of the email and pasted it into an email, but the links for the parents didn't show up as links.  I had to figure out how to convert them into links.

If i click on a book to quick look or look at the full listing, i want a way to go back to where I was (the back button brought me back to home page)    It is not clear where/when to enter the classroom code our teacher gave us.

There is no information about writing checks to pay for orders.  Why is the date not customizable? I like to collect orders on a Friday, not the set 27th which is a Wed.  Did I miss communication about these changes?    I also wish that scholastic would provide more quality resources.  Why are only a few magic tree house books included?

It is very disappointing that I have collected my own funds through donations from family, friends, and other sponsors but I am limited on which books I can make available to my students.  I have enough support to offer students a $2 book each month for 10 months.  There should be more than one book each month for me to choose from.  I understand that the cost of many things have increased but I do not think that I can create life long readers without choice of books.  In the past, the discount store opened when you spent so much.  At least then, I could offer at least three different books to my students to choose from.  Now, there is only one.  I am dedicated to my profession and using your company to receive the books for my students.  It would just be nice to be able to access more books for a discounted rate.

You've changed the way you submit book orders and I am very dissatisfied.  I can't change the due date.  Parents are being forced to order online.  Not all my parents can/want to order online.  And I am not sending you my parents' email addresses.  First, I don't have all their email addresses and second, I shouldn't be sharing other people's email addresses.  I have used Scholastic Book Clubs for 25 years, but after today, I may just give up and not order again.

You've changed the way you submit book orders and I am very dissatisfied.  I can't change the due date.  Parents are being forced to order online.  Not all my parents can/want to order online. I have used Scholastic Book Clubs for 25 years, but after today, I may just give up and not order again.
Please email teachers letting them know about the changes to the flyers.
This survey came up before I was finished.

I just wanted to share I am disappointed in the flyers this year.  There are a lot less individual books offered and the prices seem to have jumped.  In the past I have had many parents that would purchase one book in each order for their child.  They are now saying if they have to buy a bundle they will buy less often.  It will be interesting to see if less parents order books than in the past.  I am always a golden apple teacher, but I am afraid, even with a larger class, this might not happen.

would love to see more items for the bonus points. I have purchased some awesome items in the past, but it seems to hnot have the same quality items available anymore.  Preschool items like puzzles, counters, patterns and more would be great.   book choices are always wonderful!
The login screen was unresponsive for a long time. Captcha was not doing anything, but would not log me in.
What happened to the real value books? My school is such high poverty these prices are too much.

My students can't afford books. They are in a low income rural area. I get sponsors for them so they can get a book a month. With not having value packs of the same book or five pack books for a low price, I will only be able to get them a book every other month.
How do I get flyers sent to my school?
unable to read the price/points needed to purchase items.  They are garbled and written on top of each other.  I have no idea what I am looking at.
Teacher's desk completely different and not friendly
I wasnt able to find my childs teachers name under the school. So o did a live chat and the rep was able to add the teachers name right away for me to complete the order.
Your popup survey is in the middle of the process.
In the past, my families order more from paper copies because many do not order online.
I just switched grades and need to get new book orders for my students.
I'm disappointed that I cannot provide my class code on the flyer that goes home with children. There are no boxes provided to do so.
Could not find my class code anymore and am disappointed I have not gotten any flyers to send home to my families.
Could not find my class code anymore and am disappointed I have not gotten any flyers to send home to my families.

It was easier to order when we could enters student orders, families in my community do not know how to use or purchase online and or they do not have the time due to their work hours.  They are less likely to buy if they have to order on their own.

My name did not pop up on my school's site when I searched for teachers and I wanted to make sure it was listed before I sent home booklets.    I also miss seeing the regular order forms b/c some students would still send cash or check to order.

My name did not pop up on my school's site when I searched for teachers and I wanted to make sure it was listed before I sent home booklets.    I also miss seeing the regular order forms b/c some students would still send cash or check to order.

I really feel like over the last few years scholastic has really declined. As a school we always tried to provide the students with the $1 books but now with the cost increase and charging shipping/tax on the teacher order it isn't possible anymore. Shipping isn't always reliable, sometimes shipping takes so long we forget there are books coming.

I am still getting used to all of the new things on the flyer (games, art ideas, graphics, etc.). I am surprised and slightly disappointed at the prices of the items. There seems to have been a sharp increase in price. I undestand that everything is more expensive these days, but prices seemed to have doubled since last year. The quality of books has decreased over the past few years so I'm not sure if it is still worth purchasing books from Scholastic.

I am disappointed in the quality of books offered by Scholastic. I have been offering Scholastic flyers to my students for more than 30 years. The quality of the literature is poor compared to what used to be offered by Scholastic. I find it difficult to find books that I would recommend to parents now.
I was not able to change the order date or print out labels.
I wish there was a larger selection of board books for pre-k. My son is very rough and sometimes rips the pages of regular books.
I would like more Spanish books to be available.
I wish there were more books to choose from for each grade level.

I'm still learning the changes that you have made. I miss the bonus point catalog! I like to use my bonus points for things other than books most of the time and I liked having the option to go straight to the bonus catalog for this. Having to sort through all the items is too cumbersome.

I want my students to read QUALITY LITERATURE. There are way too many cartoon/movie characters and fluff. Bring back Charlotte's Web, Kate di  Camillo, and WORDS to build student vocabularies. I know my colleagues agree.
I am disappointed that the $2 books seem to no longer be an option.  This will diminish the ability for many kids to order at all and also for me to buy books for students who cannot.
I didn't experience any difficulties today but before I had a hard time logging in on my phone (I wasn't able to submit on the entry screen).
It was difficult to connect to a new teacher.
Seeing the AR Level or being able to search by AR level was not intuitive.

Difficulty setting up ewallet and moving funds from previous book fair to current wallet.  Site is not intuitive to doing that, and the video is nice but doesn't show how to navigate steps to the ewallet.
Its difficult to use the site on mobile, which was how we had to access it via QR code.
Submitting credit card and finding the right bookslimited choices
Earlier it wouldn't let me log in and it said to try again later.

The bonus points catalog is lacking the technology I have been saving my points up for years. Also, I can't find out how to order paper flyers. Our school is a title one school. Most order their books with cash. Also, with no paper flyers, it is hard to get the students excited about book orders since they have nothing to look at. The changes to Scholastic Book Clubs are extremely disappointing.
It would be nice for parents to send orders and payments back to the teacher as some parents don't have access to internet.
I couldn't find how to edit when the order was due.  In the past, I could change the due date.
I am disappointed that there aren't any choices for students beyond middle school.
Why did I have to put my DOB?

Checking to make sure my profile was correct. I only received 1 set of order forms. i have 2 classes. I also checked on bonus points for September orders as September is always a great month to order and earn points. I see that has changed.  So sad for all these changes.

Checking to make sure my profile was correct. I only received 1 set of order forms. i have 2 classes. I also checked on bonus points for September orders as September is always a great month to order and earn points. I see that has changed.  So sad for all these changes.

I'd like to be able to change my due date.  It shouldn't be set to a certain date for everyone.  I try to avoid having them due during book fair to not take away from the librarian's orders.  The September due date is set during our book fair and due on a Wednesday.  I like to set the date also on a Friday.

I'm trying to find out when my flyers are coming. We've been in school since August 16 and will be out for a Harvest Break in  3 weeks. I'd like to send flyers home and have a chance to order them before we go on break. That doesn't look like that's going to happen.
Looking for Who Is Harry Styles?
The site has so many different parts to it, it can be very confusing.

Could not print the editable letter ("bad request")  Could not change the due date - parents order more when the due date is within one week of me sending home flyers  I do NOT like the new format. Disappointed that there are no longer $1 books. Do not appreciate only online ordering for families. Prices have increased. Overall disappointed in Scholastic.

The book prices are ridiculously higher this year. Reach year your pricing gets worse that's why we now order from Amazon. Way cheaper bills and faster service and we can donate to a charity if our choice. I miss the $1 books, i miss the book of the week, i miss the code reads25 to get a free book. There are rarely anymore books under $5. I have been shopping with you for the last 6 years.... The price differences and strategies you are using are quite shocking and disappointing. You need to have cheaper books and deals like 6 years ago. I'm buying a lot less this year if the prices continue this high.

I am dissatisfied with the new format for ordering. I think parents should have the option to order from the flyer or digitally. Many of the parents in my school's community do not have the capability to order for their child on-line. I have been using Scholastic for the past 25+ years, but I will not be using your site this year.

Extremely disappointed that you are no longer offering Club Leo student catalogs. This was my and my students main source of purchasing books in Spanish. Even though my students mostly purchase books in English (because there is a far greater variety of books in English) without the Club Leo option, I will not bother offering scholastic books to my classroom this year. This is such a shame, instead of offering a better selection of books in Spanish, you wont even give them the option of getting excited about them.
